# YouTube → Roblox Bridge — Browser Extension

Syncs your active YouTube video to your Roblox experience in real time.

---

## How it works

```
YouTube tab  →  content.js scrapes metadata
                    ↓
              background.js POSTs to your server
                    ↓
              Your server stores user state
                    ↓
              Roblox polls /status/:token  →  in-game GUI updates
```

---

## Installation (Chrome / Edge / Brave)

1. Open `chrome://extensions`
2. Enable **Developer mode** (top right)
3. Click **Load unpacked**
4. Select this entire `yt-roblox-extension/` folder

The extension icon will appear in your toolbar.

---

## Setup

### 1. Add placeholder icons
Chrome requires icon files. Drop 16×16, 48×48, and 128×128 PNGs into the
`icons/` folder named `icon16.png`, `icon48.png`, `icon128.png`.
Any placeholder images work while developing.

### 2. Point it at your server
Open the extension popup and set:
- **Bridge Server URL** — the URL of your backend server (e.g. `https://your-server.com`)
- **Your Roblox Link Token** — a short code that identifies you. This is the
  same code you enter in-game with `/link` to connect your accounts.

### 3. Play a YouTube video
The badge turns green (▶) when syncing and grey (▐▐) when paused.

---

## Data sent to your server

Every update POSTs this JSON to `POST /update`:

```json
{
  "token":     "XK-4921",
  "videoId":   "dQw4w9WgXcQ",
  "title":     "Never Gonna Give You Up",
  "channel":   "Rick Astley",
  "thumbnail": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dQw4w9WgXcQ/hqdefault.jpg",
  "duration":  213,
  "position":  47,
  "paused":    false,
  "url":       "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dQw4w9WgXcQ",
  "timestamp": 1718000000000
}
```

Your server exposes `GET /status/:token` for Roblox to poll.

---

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `manifest.json` | Extension config & permissions |
| `src/content.js` | Runs on YouTube — scrapes video metadata & events |
| `src/background.js` | Service worker — receives messages, POSTs to server |
| `src/popup.html` | Extension popup UI |
| `src/popup.js` | Popup logic — settings, live now-playing display |

---

## Next steps

- **Backend server** — a simple Express/Node server that stores user state
- **Roblox scripts** — HttpService polling + RemoteEvent broadcast to all clients
- **Account linking flow** — `/link` chat command that maps tokens to Roblox UserIds
